cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "MAPLE: Multi-Agent Personalized Learning Plans"
message: "If you use MAPLE in your research, please cite the paper below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: "TBD"
    given-names: "TBD"
    affiliation: "TBD"
    # orcid: "https://orcid.org/0000-0000-0000-0000"
abstract: >-
  MAPLE is a dataset and training/evaluation pipeline for multi-agent
  personalized teaching plans. It pairs Stack Overflow duplicate-question
  clusters with learner profiles, generates multi-agent plans with Claude
  Sonnet 4.6, and validates them via static structural checks and execution
  feasibility. The release includes hierarchical SFT (PAD / SDP / Joint
  Alignment) and GRPO training code with structural + personalization +
  pedagogical + hard-constraint rewards, a CrewAI-based Teacher/Student
  Socratic execution layer, and a five-tier baseline matrix.
keywords:
  - multi-agent systems
  - personalized learning
  - large language models
  - educational AI
  - SFT
  - GRPO
license: MIT
license-url: "https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT"
repository-code: "https://github.com/preke/maple"
url: "https://github.com/preke/maple"

